node.text:
This was filmed about 2 years before I ever released the WNRS game. Even the cards look a bit different here. I took those years to continue improving the game. I was a perfectionist (still am) and obsessed over every detail of what the game is today. But that perfectionism also helped me veil how terrified  I was to release WNRS to the world. It was (and still is) my baby and I was terrified of rejection.

Fast forward to today, the game is now released. I was so terrified of that. But it’s turned out to be the best feeling seeing the game do for y’all what it’s done for me.

node.text: This was one of the most magical days I’ve ever had. We set up a public installation and invited complete strangers to play WNRS. We literally casted the day of and asked people to participate as they were walking past us. We filmed way before the game was even fully finished or out in the public. But she’s all ready now! Link in bio. 🤧❤️
